def: Of or pertaining to pitch; resembling pitch in color orquality; pitchy.
The offspring of a quadroon and a white person; a mestee.
One to whom a legacy is bequeathed.
A person who devotes himself to the spread of any system ofprinciples. "Political propagandists." Walsh.
Capable of being suspended; capable of being held from sinking.
The dominion of an ethnarch; principality and rule. Wright.
Rolled together downward, the tip occupying the center; -- aterm used in reference to foliation or leafing, as in ferns. Gray.
A product from cottonseed, used as lard.
The under side of the subordinate parts and members ofbuildings, such as staircases, entablatures, archways, cornices, orthe like. See Illust. of Lintel.
A sight covering; a scarf. See Simar.Her body shaded with a light cymar. Dryden.
To feel or express undue care and anxiety; to manifestdisquietude or pain; to be fretful; to chafe; as, the child worries;the horse worries.
One who engraves; a person whose business it is to produceengraved work, especially on metal or wood.
